      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "a8b41fbb3d02b80a9bee60a550395364b4dc51e7",
            "subject": "LU-2068 build: Respect \"--without-ldiskfs\" option"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Prakash Surya",
          "email": "surya1@llnl.gov",
          "date": "2012-09-27 22:37:10.000000000",
          "tz": -420
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
          "email": "alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com",
          "date": "2012-10-03 06:02:30.000000000",
          "tz": 240
        },
        "subject": "LU-2078 ofd: drop locking in ofd_sync",
        "message": "LU-2078 ofd: drop locking in ofd_sync\n\nImprove concurrency by dropping the write lock around\ndt_object_sync(). This is safe because all consistency\nrelated to a single object is supposed to be maintained\nby the osd internally.  In this case:\n\n  1) osd_object_sync() doesn't rely on the object at all:\n     global sync is called\n  2) even if object is being destroyed at the same time -\n     we're holding a reference, so we're safe\n  3) dt_version_get() -> osd_xattr_get() has own internal\n     locking, protecting xattr consistency to improve\n     concurrency\n\nSigned-off-by: Alex Zhuravlev <bzzz@whamcloud.com>\nSigned-off-by: Brian Behlendorf <behlendorf1@llnl.gov>\nSigned-off-by: Prakash Surya <surya1@llnl.gov>\nChange-Id: I60c5b6a1d10afc717a24e7471071f1e2fdb89c29\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
